              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target stack consisted of from 4 to 10 targets,",
                "alternating and in contact with forward catcher foils",
                "consisting of high-purity aluminum (99.999%) with an",
                "areal density of 7 mg/cm2. Aluminum degrading foils",
                "were inserted where appropriate. The targets were",
                "made by depositing a layer of barium nitrate on the",
                "above mentioned aluminum foil by an electrophoresis",
                "procedure. A suspension was prepared by mixing about",
                "5 mg of finely ground enriched barium nitrate (84.6%",
                "134Ba) in acetone. The suspension was placed in a",
                "Teflon cell and a potential of 400 V was maintained",
                "across copper electrodes for approximately one",
                "minute. The target thicknesses, determined by",
                "weighing samples of known area, were in the range",
                "from 1 to 3 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "STTA",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " After irradiation cerium was",
                "chemically separated. The disintegration rates of the",
                "isomers were determined by assay of the K X-ray",
                "activity of the samples. The measurements were",
                "performed with several thin NaI(Tl) detectors",
                "connected to single- channel analysers set to accept",
                "Ce and La K X-rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The (a,n) data at higher energies are",
                "uncertain by as much as 25% because of (a,2n)",
                "contribution. The random errors in the cross sections",
                "and recoil ranges include the uncertainties in"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": 5.0,
                "maximum_value": 10.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " target thickness (5-10%)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " chemical yields (5%)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-3",
                "minimum_value": 1.0,
                "maximum_value": 3.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " disintegration rates: 1% for 137mCe, 3%",
                "for 137gCe."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-4",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The cross sections are subject to an",
                "additional systematic error of l0% because of",
                "uncertainties in the counter efficiencies and the",
                "decay scheme. Many of the random and all of the",
                "systematic errors cancel in the calculation of the",
                "isomer ratios so that these constitute our most",
                "accurate results."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In addition, the (alpha,n) results at the higher",
                "energies are uncertain by as much as 25% because of",
                "the sizeable correction for the contribution from the",
                "135Ba(alpha,2n) reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Compiler comment: The half-lives of Ce-137g and -m",
                "are swapped by authors compared to recent data",
                "sources. According to the ENSDF database 137Ce ground",
                "state T1/2=9.0 HR and isomeric state T1/2=34.4 HR.",
                "Authors give it the other way according to the",
                "assignment of 1970."
              ]
            }
          ],
